The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Corporate Briefs

 Alstom Projects India, a subsidiary of France-based Alstom SA, has bagged three orders worth Rs 750 crore from National Hydroelectric Power Corporation (NHPC) and Gati Infrastructure to implement hydro projects. While NHPCs orders involve execution of projects for the Uri Stage-II and Chamera Stage-III, the order from Gati infrastructure was for the Chuzachen project, Alstom has informed the BSE. 

 Microsoft Corporation India Pvt Ltd had organised a roadshow in the city to educate customers and partners on the 2007 Microsoft Office System, Windows Vista and Exchange Server 2007 platform. The company will conduct seven such roadshows along with its partners Intel, AMD, EMC, Nortel, Wipro, Kingston and Sonata.

 Tech Mahindra has entered into a partnership with Sitronics Telecom Solutions, a Czech Republic company, to help telecom firms launch services. Sitronics is a developer and producer of high-end communications equipment with bases in central and eastern European markets, while Tech Mahindra is present in Asia Pacific.

 Hyderabad-based ICSA (India) Ltds board has approved foreign investments of about $52 million at an extraordinary general meeting. Citigroup Venture Capital International Growth Partnership Mauritius Ltd will acquire around 14 per cent stake in the company.

 Kotak Mahindra Mutual Fund has launched a scheme called Kotak Emerging equity scheme. The scheme is a three-year closed-end equity growth scheme. The investment objective of the scheme is to generate long-term capital appreciation from a portfolio of equity and equity-related securities.

 Eastern India Regional Council (EIRC) of the Institute of Chartered Accountants of India (ICAI) has won the Rotating Shield award for 2006 jointly with the Western India Regional Council. ICAI offers a Rotating Shield for the best regional council every year.

 Shree Cement has despatched 4.09 lakh tonnes in January 2007 against 3.12 lakh tonnes in the same period of the previous year, a growth of 31.09 per cent. In the nine-month period ended January 2007, the company had despatched 39.51 million tonnes.

